column619: guess work

If I thought my answer was correct and AI agreed with me, it re-enforced my opinion on being correct. If I got the answer wrong - according to the AI at least, I'd be somewhat skeptical of it being correct so I never fully put trust in it.

If I was confident of the answer (~30% of the time) I went with it. If something sounded plausible or implausible I made my initial guess accordingly. If the AI's explanation seemed to not relate to the question (~50% of the time), I ignored it. Otherwise, I adjusted my answer toward the AI's input based on weighing my own confidence and the reasonableness of the AI explanation. In many cases, I ended up far from confident even after adjusting.
